  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "If you look at the host/daemons view on the dashboard, every daemon is on its own \"host\" (with the hostname matching the pod name).  This isn't the reality of the cluster; the user (as least this user!) expects to see what physical hosts the daemons are on.\r\n\r\nSimilarly, this is what is used to populate the crush hierarchy, which *does* need to map to the physical hardware in order to be useful.\r\n\r\n<!-- **Are you in the right place?**\r\n1. For issues or feature requests, please create an issue in this repository.\r\n2. For general technical and non-technical questions, we are happy to help you on our [Rook.io Slack](https://Rook-io.slack.com).\r\n3. Did you already search the existing open issues for anything similar? -->\r\n\r\n**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Feature Request\r\n\r\n**What should the feature do:**\r\n\r\n**What is use case behind this feature:**\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n<!-- Specific environment information that helps with the feature request -->\r\n",
